So I've actually been eating #keto for the entire summer (with some Paleo days and one intentional stretch of "summer days special eats".

If you don't know, keto diet is a high fat, low carb and moderate protein diet. Your body converts to burn fat as it's fuel source. It's very efficient. That is why it's wildly popular.

Here's why I don't like telling people I'm doing keto. What most people know of keto they think pizza, cheese, and bacon.
I eat those things as treats only.  I personally do not believe that the fad way of doing keto (üçïüßÄüç≥ü•ì) is a healthy option for me but keto can have a lot of health benefits when done with holistic health in mind. 

I prefer to follow @drterrywahls Wahl's Paleo Plus which is a nutritional ketogenic diet that focuses on eating for brain health and healing. The main source of your fat is from coconut milk which has medium chain triglycerides. This allows you to up your net carbs...
IN LAYMANS TERMS PLEASEüòÖ

More coconut milk allows for more veggies = happy me.

My diet is usually: a smoothie with coconutmilk @northcoastnaturals
All-In-One for breakfast plus spinach and/or avocado and maca powder. Lunch is a smoothie as well if I'm working or a salad if I'm home with dressing, sunflower seeds, cucumbers and chicken or turkey. Dinner is random but often with side veggies. Dessert is usually coconut pudding or icecream. Snacks are usually carrots, cucumber, zuchinni or nuts. 

For the next month or so I'm going to follow the meal plans in @leannevogel s The Keto Diet book. There's still not as many veggies as I prefer but I love love love how it breaks it down into calories and nutritional information, and I can probably sneak more veggies in.

There is no perfect "diet". But, there are important things to consider as we approach changes to support our goals. I do think the keto diet can have a lot of flaws, but I also see how and when it can be beneficial

Even thought weightloss is an important goal for my health, it needs to be approached in healthy and sustainable ways.

There we go, all honesty. 
